quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  21,51,"And We had given Abraham his correct/right guidance from before, and We were with (about) him knowing"
  21,52,"When he said to his father and to his nation: \"What (are) these the statues which you are to it devoting/dedicating"
  21,53,"They said: \"We found our fathers to it worshipping"
  21,54,"He said: \"You had been, you and your fathers in clear/evident misguidance"
  21,55,"They said: \"Did you come to us with the truth , or you are from the playing amusing"
  21,56,"He said: \"But your Lord (is) the skies`/space`s and the earth`s/Planet Earth`s Lord, who created them (B) ,and I am on that from the witnessing/testifying"
  21,57,"And by God, I will manipulate/fight/(destroy) (E) your idols/statues , after that you turn giving (your) backs"
  21,58,"So he made them broken/pieces except a big/large (one) for them, maybe/perhaps to it they return"
  21,59,"They said: \"Who made/did that with our Gods? That he is from (E) the unjust/oppressive"
  21,60,"They said: \"We heard a youth/adolescent mentioning them, is said to him, Abraham"
  21,61,"They said: \"So come/bring with him on the people`s eyes/sights, maybe/perhaps they witness/testify"
  21,62,"They said: \"Did you make/do this with our Gods, you Abraham"
  21,63,"He said: \"But/rather their oldest/biggest , that, made/did it, so ask/question them, if they were speaking"
  21,64,"So they returned to themselves, so they said: \"That you are, you are the unjust/oppressive"
  21,65,"Then they were turned upside down on their heads/tops, \"You had known those do not speak"
  21,66,"He said: \"Do you worship from other than God what does not benefit you a thing, and nor harm you"
  21,67,"Ugh to you, and to what you worship from other than God, so do you not reason/comprehend"
  21,68,"They said: \"Burn him, and give victory/aid (to) your gods, if you were making/doing (that)"
  21,69,"We said: \"You fire, be/become cool/cold and peaceful/safe on Abraham"
  21,70,"And they intended with him a plot/conspiracy/deceit , so We made them the most losers"
  21,71,And We saved/rescued him and Lot to the Earth/land which We blessed in it to the creations all together/(universes)
  21,72,"And We granted to him Isaac and Jacob gifts , each/all, We made correct/righteous"
  21,73,"And We made them leaders/examples guiding with Our order/command, and We inspired/transmitted to them making/doing the goodnesses , and keeping up the prayers, and giving/bringing the charity/purification , and they were to Us worshipping"
  21,74,"And Lot, We gave/brought him judgment/rule and knowledge, and We saved/rescued him from the village/urban city which was making/doing the bad/forbidden , that they truly were a bad/evil nation (of) debauchers"
  21,75,"And We entered him in Our mercy, that he truly (is) from the correct/righteous"